  "texts": [
    "Therefore, it is widely used for analyzing qualitative data.",
    "The thematic analysis involves the identification of patterns and the subsequent organization of these patterns into themes relevant to the research topics.",
    "Initially, the interview data underwent open coding, with initial labels applied to different segments, known as 1st order codes, facilitating the identification of potential themes.",
    "Comparable labels were then grouped under distinct categories and represented by 2nd order codes, enabling aggregation-related concepts and patterns.",
    "Through iterative grouping and categorization, the categories were further organized into aggregated themes, which formed the focus of the analysis."
  ],
